{{Phenomenon Class|danger=5|effectiveness=5|frequency=?}}

<div style="background-color: #2E0000; padding: 1em; border-radius: 16px;">
<div style="background-color:#3D0000; padding: 1em; border-radius: 8px; margin: 15px 15px 15px 15px;">
==DESCRIPTION==
Phenomenon 306, colloquially referred to as "crimson whirls" or "blood storms", manifests within [[:Category:Levels|levels]] with an open, or visible sky. Red in colour, it appears similar to that of a hurricane— large supercell-like clouds forming high above. Thick red fog is often associated with the phenomenon and acts as one of 3 precursors to its formation. The fog is theorised to be vapourised bromine, which is toxic to the lungs and eyes. Swirling, dark-red clouds often form before its manifestation, serving as the second precursor. The third precursor is often described as a pounding, continued headache of intermediate length. This effect has often been accompanied by tinnitus and hearing loss, acting as one's last warning. Manifestations occur "globally", affecting areas rather than localised, personal manifestations.

Air quality during its manifestation is notably decreased, with the air converting oxygen into heavy gases akin to xenon & bromine. These have been proven toxic for inhalation, and is not recommended. High-level gas masks are required for study, due to this.

{{Blurimage|file=phen306blood.jpg|caption=A blood storm of notable size, determined to be P7 on the Poller Scale.}}

Each blood storm is determined by the Poller Scale, devised by physicist James Poller. The number is determined by its width, length & wind power. Storms of small-scale are P0 or P1, depending on wind strength. Storms of medium-scale can scale from P2 to P5, with wind speeds between 35mph and 100mph. P6 through P8 storms can range largely in scale, from 2 miles in width to 1,000 miles in width. P9 is purely theoretical: ranging across an entire level. P10 has also been theorised, though unlikely, to affect the entirety of the [[Backrooms Wiki|Backrooms]]<ref>Similarly to [[Phenomenon 12|The Flicker]].</ref>.

Upon the manifestation of a Blood Storm, elements of the level may become red in colour, and objects may react in unique ways. These reactions are outlined below.
