Blood Storms have been found to have a 100% mortality rate; victims' bodies were often found malformed and disfigured<ref>During [[Phenomenon 12|the Flicker]], all affected individuals were cured and spared. It is unknown as to why this happened or how.</ref>.
</div>

<div style="background-color:#3D0000; padding: 1em; border-radius: 8px; margin: 15px 15px 15px 15px;>
==AFFLICTION==
In the event of a full manifestation, all affected individuals will be afflicted with Baphomets Curse, outlined below.
===PHASE 1===
Upon the commitment of a sin, phase 1 will begin. During phase 1, victims may feel a multitude of effects, including:
* Nausea;
* Vomiting;
* Blurry Vision;
* Dizzyness;
* Headaches;
* Confusion.

During this phase, internal bleeding begins, and individual blood vessels begin breaking down into erythrocytes. Dizziness, confusion, vomiting, headaches & blurry vision are all effects of internal bleeding within the encephalon. In contrast, vomiting and nausea are caused by small, micrometre-sized holes forming within the stomach lining.

These are just some of the effects, acting as a precursor to Phases 2, 3 & 4.
===PHASE 2===
~24 hours following Phase 1, Phase 2 will begin. A majority of the victims' blood vessels will begin breaking down at an accelerated rate compared to Phase 1. Effects of this phase include:
* Accelerated breaking down of blood vessels;
* Memory loss;
* Strokes;
* Seizures.

Strokes & memory loss occur from infarction, as the brain becomes deprived of oxygen and glucose.
===PHASE 3===
~48 hours following the affliction, affected individuals organs will begin to break down into their primary components, the nervous system will have likely already broken down, recovery past this point is impossible.
===PHASE 4===
Phase 4 involves the entire decomposition of the bone, skin, & muscle. Reddish brown particulates remain following the decomposition, covering the ground in dust. It is believed these particulates are the remains of the brain, as it has shown slowed decomposition.

</div>

<div style="background-color:#3D0000; padding: 1em; border-radius: 8px; margin: 15px 15px 15px 15px;">
==FORMATION==
Blood Storms form only upon the breakage of any law, guideline, or restriction. The phenomenon comes with its own set of theorised laws, known as the Lamb laws. There is a small window for a Blood Storm to form; if it does not form within this timeframe, it will not form at all.

As aforementioned, there are 4 discovered guidelines that may cause a Blood Storm. These are outlined below.

* [[The Void|Noclippage]] into substances with an identical colour to that of blood. Consistency and molecular structure are ignored.
* Maliciously taking the life of a living being, be it flora or fauna, may manifest the phenomenon.
* The burning of a baby lamb's wool may manifest a Blood Storm.
* Desecration of religious imagery, ranging from images to objects, has a guaranteed chance to manifest a Blood Storm.

Each "sin" committed will cause an audible, ~76 decibel bell to ring. It is undeterminable of the location of this bell, with the sound manifesting across the entire level. The severity of each sin committed depends on the number of bell tolls<!--for whom the bell tolls ahh-->, with Noclippage being the least severe at one toll, and desecration being the most severe at 6 tolls. Taking another's life comes at 2 tolls, with the burning of a baby lamb's wool coming at 4 tolls. Upon the commiting of a sin, it is recommended to wear protective gear to avoid permanent hearing damage and loss.

Each broken sin has a chance to manifest a blood storm, outlined below.

